text: Ismael Musallami (, born 31 January 1989) is a Saudi Arabian professional footballer who plays as a midfielder . ==Career== Musallami he started his career at the youth team of Hetten and he arrived for the first team in 2009 . and landed with Hetten from the Saudi First Division to the Saudi Second Division in 2014-15 season . Musallami left Hetten and signed with Najran on May 20, 2015, but he did not play with them and the contract was canceled . signed with Al-Hazem on July 18, 2016 . left Al-Hazem and signed with Al-Ain on July 6, 2019 . ==References== == External links == * Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:Saudi Arabian footballers Category:Hetten FC players Category:Najran SC players Category:Al-Hazem F.C. players Category:Al- Ain FC (Saudi Arabia) players Category:Saudi Professional League players Category:Prince Mohammad bin Salman League players Category:Association football midfielders
